.Dd May 3, 2026
.Dt CRATED 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm crated
.Nd REST API daemon for remote crate(8) management
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl f
.Op Fl c Ar config
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
exposes the read and write halves of the
.Xr crate 8
control surface over HTTP/HTTPS, so external tooling
.Pq the hub web dashboard, CI runners, monitoring agents
can drive container lifecycle without an interactive shell on the host.
.Pp
The daemon listens on three independent endpoints:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Unix domain socket
Local-only access, default
.Pa /var/run/crate/crated.sock .
A connecting peer is currently treated as
.Em admin
on the assumption that the socket file mode
.Pq Pa root:wheel No 0660
is the access control.
.It TCP listener
TLS-capable. Default port 9800. Authentication via
.Ar Authorization: Bearer <token>
header against the token list in
.Pa crated.conf .
.It WebSocket console
Independent TCP listener on
.Ar console_ws.port
.Pq default 0, disabled .
Implements RFC 6455 v13. After the upgrade handshake the daemon
proxies bytes between the WebSocket and a
.Xr jexec 8 Ns 'd
.Pa /bin/sh -i
running inside the target jail.
.El
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl f , Fl Fl foreground
Stay in the foreground; do not fork off the controlling terminal.
Useful when running under
.Xr daemon 8
or systemd-style supervisors.
.It Fl c Ar config , Fl Fl config Ar config
Path to the YAML configuration file. Default
.Pa /usr/local/etc/crated.conf .
.El
.Sh ENDPOINTS
.Bl -tag -width "DELETE /api/v1/exports/:filename                 "
.It GET Pa /healthz
Liveness check. No auth.
.It GET Pa /api/v1/containers
List running jails (delegates to
.Xr jls 8
.Fl Fl libxo Ar json ) .
.It GET Pa /api/v1/host
Host-level info: kernel release, hostname, ncpu, physmem.
.It GET Pa /metrics
Prometheus exposition. No auth, rate-limited.
.It GET Pa /api/v1/containers/:name/stats
Snapshot RCTL counters for the named container.
.It GET Pa /api/v1/containers/:name/stats/stream
Server-sent events stream of stats, 1 Hz.
.It GET Pa /api/v1/containers/:name/logs
Tail container console log;
.Ar ?follow=true
holds the connection open.
.It POST Pa /api/v1/containers/:name/start
Resume a container from its
.Pa /var/run/crate/<name>.crate
file.
.It POST Pa /api/v1/containers/:name/stop
Send SIGTERM, then SIGKILL after a grace window.
.It POST Pa /api/v1/containers/:name/restart
Stop + start in one call.
.It DELETE Pa /api/v1/containers/:name
Destroy the jail and remove its dataset.
.It GET Pa /api/v1/containers/:name/snapshots
List ZFS snapshots for the container.
.It POST Pa /api/v1/containers/:name/snapshots
Create a snapshot. Body
.Pq optional :
.Ic { Qq name : Qq <snap> } .
Without a body, an
.Ar auto_YYYY-MM-DD_HHMMSS
name is generated.
.It DELETE Pa /api/v1/containers/:name/snapshots/:snap
Delete a snapshot.
.It POST Pa /api/v1/containers/:name/export
Run
.Ic tar | xz
on the live rootfs and write
.Pa /var/run/crate/<name>-<unixtime>.crate .
Returns
.Ic { file , size , sha256 } .
.It GET Pa /api/v1/exports/:filename
Stream a previously-exported
.Pa .crate
back to the client.
.It POST Pa /api/v1/imports/:name
Accept a raw
.Pa .crate
body
.Pq Ic Content-Type: application/octet-stream
and atomic-rename into
.Pa /var/run/crate/<name>.crate .
.It GET Pa /api/v1/containers/:name/console
.Pq WebSocket
Interactive
.Pa /bin/sh
session inside the named jail.
.El
.Sh AUTHENTICATION
Read endpoints are open to local socket peers and to any
.Em viewer
or
.Em admin
token holder. Mutating endpoints require an
.Em admin
token, except over the unix socket where
.Po
see
.Sx CAVEATS
.Pc
all peers are currently admin.
.Pp
Tokens are stored as
.Ar sha256:<hex>
hashes in
.Pa crated.conf ;
the daemon never sees the plaintext after first run.
.Sh CONFIGURATION
The default config path is
.Pa /usr/local/etc/crated.conf
(YAML). Sample structure:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
listen:
    unix: /var/run/crate/crated.sock
    tcp_port: 9800
    tcp_bind: 0.0.0.0

tls:
    cert: /usr/local/etc/crated.crt
    key:  /usr/local/etc/crated.key
    require_client_cert: false

auth:
    tokens:
      - name:        ci-runner
        token_hash:  sha256:abc123...
        role:        admin

console_ws:
    port: 9802
    bind: "::"

log:
    file:  /var/log/crated.log
    level: info
.Ed
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "/usr/local/etc/crated.conf.sample"
.It Pa /usr/local/etc/crated.conf
Operator-edited config file.
.It Pa /usr/local/etc/crated.conf.sample
Pristine reference shipped with the package.
.It Pa /var/run/crate/crated.sock
Unix domain control socket.
.It Pa /var/run/crate/crated.pid
Process id of the daemon.
.It Pa /var/run/crate/<name>.crate
Saved container archives produced by the export endpoint and
consumed by the start endpoint.
.It Pa /var/log/crated.log
Default log file.
.El
.Sh CAVEATS
.Bl -bullet
.It
Unix-socket peers are currently treated as admin without
verifying their uid/gid via
.Xr getpeereid 2 .
The unix-socket file mode is the only access control. A future
release will tighten this.
.It
The WebSocket console listener is disabled by default
.Pq Ar console_ws.port = 0 .
.It
TLS configuration is operator-supplied. The daemon will not
auto-generate certificates.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr crate 5 ,
.Xr crate-hub 8 ,
.Xr crate-snmpd 8 ,
.Xr jexec 8 ,
.Xr jls 8
